The Amathole water supply crisis in the mostly rural authority has been worsened by the drought which has resulted in the municipality spending more than R1.5-million a day trucking water to the worst-affected towns.The amounts are contained in a council agenda for August.In the Mnquma Municipality alone Amathole spends about R600 000 a day carting water to Butterwoth Centane and Ngqamakhwe.More in The Herald TMG Digital/ The Herald